A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 26 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 nurses, so as provide for a certified registered nurse anesthetist to order and administer
3 anesthesia and an anesthesia plan under certain conditions; to provide for definitions; to
4 provide for liability; to provide for a healthcare facility to adopt policies relating to the
5 provision of anesthesia; to provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date; to
6 repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Chapter 26 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to nurses, is
10 amended by revising Code Section 43-26-11.1, relating to administration of anesthesia by
11 certified registered nurse anesthetist, as follows:
12 "43-26-11.1.
13 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
14 (1) 'Anesthesia plan' means a plan for anesthesia care, including, but not limited to,
15 evaluating a patient, referring a patient to other healthcare providers when necessary,
