16 choosing the appropriate anesthetic agent and technique, and ordering medications and
17 tests before, during, and after the administration of anesthesia.
18 (2) 'Coordination' means the process in which a physician and certified registered nurse
19 anesthetist work together to manage a patient's care, including, but not limited to, sharing
20 information, discussing a patient's diagnosis, condition, and treatment, and developing
21 and modifying an anesthesia plan to ensure the best possible delivery of healthcare.
22 (b) In any case where it is lawful for a duly licensed physician practicing medicine under
23 the laws of this state to administer anesthesia, such anesthesia and an anesthesia plan may
24 be ordered and administered by a certified registered nurse anesthetist, provided that such
25 anesthesia is administered under the direction and responsibility of a duly licensed
26 physician in coordination with a physician licensed to practice medicine in this state.
27 (c) Nothing in this Code section shall be construed to restrict the authority of a healthcare
28 facility to adopt policies relating to the provision of anesthesia.
29 (d) A physician licensed to practice medicine in this state who is not providing the delivery
30 of anesthesia shall not be liable for an act or omission of a certified registered nurse
31 anesthetist administering anesthesia pursuant to subsection (b) of this Code section."
32 SECTION 2.
33 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
34 without such approval.
35 SECTION 3.
36 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
